        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 2:11AM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 211 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Haswell, or 37 miles northeast of North La Junta, moving east at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Haswell.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
